// with comprehensive E2E tests for all Tuple methods.
//
// For now, automated Tuple coverage is limited to:
// 1. Basic Tuple reflection (class / respondsTo:) in Erlang runtime unit tests
//    (runtime/apps/beamtalk_runtime/test/beamtalk_primitive_tests.erl).
// 2. Tuple operations (at:, unwrap*, asString) in runtime unit tests
//    (runtime/apps/beamtalk_runtime/test/beamtalk_tuple_tests.erl).
// 3. This placeholder E2E file, which currently has no direct Tuple literals or methods.
//
// Planned tests (when tuple literals are available):
// - Size: {}, {a}, {a, b, c}
// - Access: at: (1-based indexing)
// - Pattern matching: isOk, isError
